# Social Media Do's and Don'ts for College Students

## DO's ✅
1. Keep your profiles professional and up to date
2. Use LinkedIn to connect with professors and industry professionals
3. Think before you post — ask yourself if you would show it to your parents
4. Use privacy settings to control who sees your content
5. Share your academic achievements and projects online
6. Follow and engage with educators and industry leaders
7. Use your real name on professional platforms like LinkedIn and GitHub

## DON'Ts ❌
1. Never share your OTP, password, or personal banking details online
2. Do not post offensive, political, or controversial content
3. Never accept friend requests from unknown people
4. Do not share your location publicly in real time
5. Avoid using social media during lectures or exams
6. Never impersonate someone else online
7. Do not engage with or spread fake news and misinformation
